            },
            "AINote|7b7af549-00ca-4a72-8947-9bf553ba4e16": {
                "quote": "Only intermittently, although with gradually increasing intensity and frequency, did the prophetic demand for the worship of Yah\u00ad weh as the one and only god make itself be heard and was it heeded by the people and their leaders.",
                "note": "This quote illustrates how religious changes under Solomon led to a gradual shift in social norms, reducing the influence of goddess Asherah. This process reflects the beginnings of male-dominated monotheism that may have contributed to the development of patriarchal societies with attendant sexism.",
